From 3b1bf2b148577c5538f787b0da494dde85e438c7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VTK Compatibility <vtk@vtk.org>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 22:22:20 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] OpenGL: Add GL 2.0 fallbacks for basic rendering

Add fallback support for OpenGL 2.0 systems where GL 3.0+ features
like glGetStringi and GL_NUM_EXTENSIONS are not available.

Key changes:
- Add helper function to parse GL version from GL_VERSION string
- Add fallback to glGetString(GL_EXTENSIONS) when glGetStringi unavailable
- Lower minimum GL version check from 3.2 to 2.0 with warnings
- Add GL version detection fallback for GL_MAJOR_VERSION/GL_MINOR_VERSION

Files modified:
- Rendering/OpenGL2/vtkOpenGLRenderWindow.cxx (base class)
- Rendering/OpenGL2/vtkCocoaRenderWindow.mm (Cocoa backend)
- Rendering/OpenGL2/vtkOSOpenGLRenderWindow.cxx (OSMesa backend)

Note: Full rendering may still require GL 3.2+ features, but this allows
basic initialization and capability reporting on older systems.
